  "text": "As we rejected in Section 3 the criticism of Frewer and Khujadze given in paragraph E4, the transformation X 6 from [CITATION_1] (translation of y(x) by a constant) is formally admitted as a symmetry of the Hopf-Burgers equation. However, if we assume that the test functions y(x) should decay asymptotically to 0 at infinity, symmetry X 6 breaks.",
